2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 47
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
SPECIAL DAY/WEEK/MONTH. Designates Wednesday, April 8, 2026 as Delta Sigma
Theta Sorority, Incorporated Day at the Louisiana State Capitol.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated Day
3 at the Louisiana State Capitol.
4 WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority was founded on January 13, 1913, by
5 twenty-two collegiate women at Howard University who sought to use their collective
6 strength to promote academic excellence, provide scholarships and support to those in need,
7 educate and stimulate participation in the establishment of positive public policy, and
8 address issues affecting their communities; and
9 WHEREAS, since its founding, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority has been committed to
10 civic engagement and public service, including historic efforts to promote voter education,
11 civil rights, and participation in the democratic process while encouraging leadership and
12 advocacy in communities across the nation; and
13 WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority was incorporated in 1930 and is a private,
14 nonprofit organization that provides assistance and support through established programs
15 in local communities and throughout the world; and
16 WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated is the largest African
17 American Greek-letter sorority, a sisterhood of more than three hundred fifty thousand
18 predominantly African American college-educated women, comprised of more than one
