1 thousand fifty chapters worldwide; and
2 WHEREAS, Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated maintains a strong presence
3 throughout the state of Louisiana, with numerous alumnae and collegiate chapters actively
4 serving their communities through programs focused on education, health, economic
5 empowerment, and civic engagement; and
6 WHEREAS, the members of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated stand on the
7 shoulders of giants, including former state representatives Renee Gill Pratt, Rosalind
8 Peychaud, Jalila Jefferson Bullock, and the late Pinkie Carolyn Wilkerson, and former state
9 senators Diana E. Bajoie, Karen Carter Peterson, and Cheryl Gray Evans, whose leadership
10 has left an enduring imprint on the history of this state; and
11 WHEREAS, membership in this highly regarded, service-based sorority also includes
12 Louisiana Senate Secretary Yolanda J. Dixon; and
13 WHEREAS, to uplift, encourage, and develop the global community, Delta Sigma
14 Theta Sorority, Incorporated focuses its efforts on the Five-Point Programmatic Thrust of
15 Economic Development, Educational Development, International Awareness and
16 Involvement, Physical and Mental Health, and Political Awareness and Involvement; and
17 WHEREAS, the organizational structure and governance of Delta Sigma Theta
18 Sorority, Incorporated is vested in the Grand Chapter, which meets at a biennial national
19 convention, and regional conferences held in the organization's seven geographic regions
20 during nonconvention years; and
21 WHEREAS, the success of the public service programs of Delta Sigma Theta
22 Sorority, Incorporated exemplifies the organization's commitment to community service and
23 academic achievement, as well as its quest for excellence in all endeavors.
24 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
25 does hereby designate Wednesday, April 8, 2026, as Delta Sigma Theta Sorority,
26 Incorporated Day at the Louisiana State Capitol; commend and recognize the women of
27 Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Incorporated for their exceptional achievements and manifold
28 contributions; and extend enduring appreciation to the organization and its members for the
29 tremendous pride and honor they bring to their local communities, the state of Louisiana, and
30 the United States of America.
